 is `d + 1`.\n\n- The lowest common ancestor of a set `S` of nodes, is the node `A` with the largest depth such that every node in `S` is in the subtree with root `A`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"alt":"Problem image","contentType":"image/png","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1123-lowest-common-ancestor-of-deepest-leaves/1123-sketch1.png","sequence":1,"sha256":"887db3bf163081d847635549cd7ca0c40a0a52a2d66bdae24a24e961c8be16e5","type":"image"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Input: root = [3,5,1,6,2,0,8,null,null,7,4]\nOutput: [2,7,4]\nExplanation: We return the node with value 2, colored in yellow in the diagram.\nThe nodes coloured in blue are the deepest leaf-nodes of the tree.\nNote that nodes 6, 0, and 8 are also leaf nodes, but the depth of them is 2, but the depth of nodes 7 and 4 is 3.","type":"code"},{"sequence":3,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":4,"text":"Input: root = [1]\nOutput: [1]\nExplanation: The root is the deepest node in the tree, and it's the lca of itself.","type":"code"},{"sequence":5,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":6,"text":"Input: root = [0,1,3,null,2]\nOutput: [2]\nExplanation: The deepest leaf node in the tree is 2, the lca of one node is itself.","type":"code"},{"sequence":7,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- The number of nodes in the tree will be in the range `[1, 1000]`.\n\n- `0 <= Node.val <= 1000`\n\n- The values of the nodes in the tree are **unique**.\n\n**Note:** This question is the same as 865: [https://leetcode.com/problems/smallest-subtree-with-all-the-deepest-nodes/](https://leetcode.com/problems/smallest-subtree-with-all-the-deepest-nodes/)","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Hash Table","Tree","Depth-First Search","Breadth-First Search","Binary Tree"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Medium","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given the `root` of a binary tree, return *the lowest common ancestor of its deepest leaves*.\n\nRecall that:\n\n- The nod