:[],"categories":["Array","Binary Search"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given an integer array `nums` sorted in non-decreasing order and an integer `target`, return `true` *if* `target` *is a **majority** element, or *`false`* otherwise*.\n\nA **majority** element in an array `nums` is an element that appears more than `nums.length / 2` times in the array.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [2,4,5,5,5,5,5,6,6], target = 5\nOutput: true\nExplanation: The value 5 appears 5 times and the length of the array is 9.\nThus, 5 is a majority element because 5 > 9/2 is true.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [10,100,101,101], target = 101\nOutput: false\nExplanation: The value 101 appears 2 times and the length of the array is 4.\nThus, 101 is not a majority element because 2 > 4/2 is false.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length <= 1000`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i], target <= 10⁹`\n\n- `nums` is sorted in non-decreasing order.","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Binary Search"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given an integer array `nums` sorted in non-decreasing order and an integer `target`, return `true` *if* `target` *is a **majority** element, or *`false`* otherwise*.\n\nA **majority** element in an array `nums` is an element that appears more than `nums.length / 2` times in the array.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [2,4,5,5,5,5,5,6,6], target = 5\nOutput: true\nExplanation: The value 5 appears 5 times and the length of the array is 9.\nThus, 5 is a majority element because 5 > 9/2 is true.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [10,100,101,101], target = 101\nOutput: false\nExplanation: The value 101 appears 2 times and the length of the array is 4.\nThus, 101 is not a majority element because 2 > 4/2 is false.\n\